      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BRAND HER BOLD (5) couldn't keep up with the smart Mathematician on debut but that's no fair task. Still did a good job to finish midfield. The subsequent form from the race has been good and she's trialled well in-between. Draws well and is a major player. JUXTAPOSE (8) was left with too much to do when resuming public elect at Murray Bridge but did warm nicely late. Drawn kinder second-up and has kept the legs ticking over with a trial between runs. Gets in light with the claim and should be very competitive. GERACE (2) returns for the Lacy camp and looks to have come back in good order, assessing her jumpout in readiness. Expect her to burn across from the wide draw and give backers a sight. KAYLA KRUZEN (9) didn't fire a shot on debut before being spelled immediately. First run in 318 days, so may need the run but her two jumpouts in readiness suggest she's forward enough and the 3kg claim gets her in light at the weights. Is well placed to make a bright return.",
